new.description: A PowerShell script to temporarily mitigate the CVE-2024-38063 vulnerability by disabling IPv6 on Windows systems. new.name: OpenSSH-CVE-2024-6387-Fix
new.description: A Bash script to mitigate the CVE-2024-6387 vulnerability in OpenSSH by providing an option to upgrade to a secure version or apply a temporary workaround. This repository helps secure systems against potential remote code execution risks associated with affected OpenSSH versions.

update.name: CVE-2024-25600-Bricks-Builder-plugin-for-WordPress
update.description: This tool is designed to exploit the CVE-2024-25600 vulnerability found in the Bricks Builder plugin for WordPress. The vulnerability allows for unauthenticated remote code execution on affected websites. The tool automates the exploitation process by retrieving nonces and sending specially crafted requests to execute arbitrary commands.
